<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Banker chats</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One basic element of the job of a bank=
er or salesperson is that you want to befriend your clients. You don=E2=80=
=99t have to have a real, close friendship with every client, but in genera=
l the more your clients feel that they have social and personal ties to you=
, the better off you are. A lot of what you are doing is fairly commoditize=
d, so it is good for clients to feel some sense of personal obligation to y=
ou so that they=E2=80=99ll send that business to you rather than to one of =
your dozen interchangeable competitors. And a lot of what isn=E2=80=99t com=
moditized is=C2=A0complicated or risky; if your clients trust you personall=
y =E2=80=94=C2=A0if they think of you not as a salesperson for Bank X but a=
s a person whom they know and like =E2=80=94=C2=A0then they will be more li=
kely to buy complicated or risky stuff from=C2=A0 you.</p><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">It is possible to build a personal rapport with a client exclus=
ively using emails from your work account, Bloomberg chats and phone calls =
from a recorded office line. People do this all the time. Traditionally, th=
ough, there is also an element of going out for dinner or drinks or golf or=
 sporting events. These things are complicated; plenty of clients don=E2=80=
=99t=C2=A0<em>want=C2=A0</em>to spend their after-work time hanging out wit=
h salespeople, and in many cases you will build a better rapport by keeping=
 everything on business channels during business hours. But certainly a lot=
 of people try the dinners-and-drinks approach, which suggests that it ofte=
n works.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One vague theory that I have=
 is that due to (1) Covid-19 and (2) everyone being increasingly online all=
 the time anyway, there has been some substitution here, where now the way =
to signify a personal friendship with clients is not so much playing golf w=
ith them but rather following them on Instagram or messaging them on WhatsA=
pp or whatever. Like, in either case what you are doing is something in the=
 category of =E2=80=9Changing out with the client in non-work ways, thus de=
epening your personal relationship.=E2=80=9D And in either case you are of =
course mixing work and non-work: When you are golfing together, you do not =
discuss deals=C2=A0<em>much</em>, but you discuss deals=C2=A0<em>a little</=
em>, and your discussions are especially impactful because you are on the g=
olf course together so you must be friends. Same in the Instagram DMs or wh=
atever.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That is not the only thing go=
ing on here, but I do think that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/28054388.266603/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvMGNhYTA2=
OTAtMTAyMC00MGI4LTgzYmYtMWRiMjdhZmU5ZWQ2/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBda33016c"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">it is=C2=A0<em>a=C2=A0</em>thing going on here</a>:</p><blockquote=
><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A senior Credit Suisse investment banker was =
removed from his position earlier this year after he was found to have used=
 unapproved messaging applications with clients, according to people with k=
nowledge of the matter.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anthony Kontoleon, =
known as =E2=80=9CAK=E2=80=9D to colleagues, was Credit Suisse=E2=80=99s gl=
obal head of equity capital markets syndicate in New York and left his posi=
tion in April. He is set to depart the bank, where he has worked for 28 yea=
rs.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The action taken by Credit Suisse comes=
 amid a US government investigation of record-keeping practices across Wall=
 Street.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Credit Suisse decided to remove Ko=
ntoleon from his role after an audit of several dozen of its bankers found =
that he had used personal messaging applications to communicate with client=
s, the people added. The audit did not find that Kontoleon had shared any i=
nappropriate information. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Syndica=
te desks, such as the one where Kontoleon worked, are attracted to text mes=
saging for quick and easy communication because they are in constant dialog=
ue with hedge fund and asset management clients about stock sales and marke=
t activity.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The practice became more common=
 when bankers started working from home during the Covid-19 crisis.</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CDuring the pandemic, people got so accust=
omed to just texting outside of the controlled environment,=E2=80=9D said o=
ne senior Wall Street banker.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
There are lots of reasons to use unregulated messaging apps to communicate =
with clients. One is that they are quick and easy, possibly quicker than us=
ing your work email or other official channels. I guess another is that you=
 can do secret crimes on those apps, though I doubt that that is relevant f=
or=C2=A0<em>most=C2=A0</em>people. But a third is that if you have a client=
=E2=80=99s personal cell number you are just a little bit closer to that cl=
ient than if you are emailing her on her work email, and that is good. Exce=
pt that it=E2=80=99s also bad.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One question=
 about unapproved texting apps is how much they substitute for official tex=
t-based electronic communications like email (which are traditionally prese=
rved, monitored, easily searchable, heavily regulated), how much they subst=
itute for <em>telephone=C2=A0</em>communications (which are often but not a=
lways preserved, and somewhat less legible to regulators), and how much the=
y substitute for <em>in-person=C2=A0</em>communications (which are basicall=
y invisible to regulators). If you used to sit around with your colleagues =
making jokes and discussing business in person, and then you all started wo=
rking from home and making jokes and discussing business in a WhatsApp chat=
, you=E2=80=99re not really <em>hiding=C2=A0</em>anything that you weren=E2=
=80=99t hiding already: Either way, you are making the jokes and discussing=
 the business in ways that are not electronically monitored by your bank. B=
