bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> talked yesterday</a> about t=
he fact that sometimes acquirers agree to buy companies, and then the marke=
t crashes before the deal closes, and they get cold feet. Since the market =
has been crashing recently, and since there are several high-profile acquis=
itions pending (oh fine there=E2=80=99s one, it=E2=80=99s Twitter), this is=
 a topic of renewed interest these days, and we discussed the strategies th=
at acquirers can use to wriggle out of deals and that targets can use to ke=
ep them in deals.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is a paper from Davi=
dson Heath and Mark Mitchell about =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/28054388.266603/aHR0cHM6Ly9wYXBlcnMuc3Nybi5jb20vc=
